                <h1>Who Was Moses? A Biblical Leader Explained</h1>
                <p>Moses was a key biblical figure, considered a prophet in Judaism, Christianity, and Islam. He is known for leading the Israelites out of slavery in Egypt, receiving the Ten Commandments on Mount Sinai, and guiding his people towards the Promised Land. His story is foundational in religious teachings and cultural history.</p>
